    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Grate your <strong>potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-golden-rosti-with-sausages-and-onion-gravy/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>grated potato </strong>to the middle of a tea towel and bring the four corners together to form a ball, then twist the ball and squeeze out as much liquid as you can</p><p>Add the <strong>squeezed potato</strong> to a bowl with a 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong>, a very generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>r\u00f6sti mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-golden-rosti-with-sausages-and-onion-gravy/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Line an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>with <strong>baking paper</strong></p><p>Spoon the <strong>r\u00f6sti mix</strong> into the dish and press firmly using your hand or the back of a spoon until the mix is compacted</p><p>Put the dish to one side of a baking tray and put in the oven for an initial 20-25 min or until the r\u00f6sti is starting to go golden around the edges</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-golden-rosti-with-sausages-and-onion-gravy/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> sliced onion</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> (or two!) with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong>,<strong> </strong>scrunch the foil around the onion to form a tightly sealed parcel</p><p>Trim your <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Cut a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong> into small pieces</p><p>Chop your<strong> chives </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-golden-rosti-with-sausages-and-onion-gravy/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>r\u00f6sti </strong>has had 20-25 min, remove the tray from the oven and add your<strong> hot dog sausage[s]</strong> and <strong>butter pieces </strong>to the top of the r\u00f6sti</p><p>Add the <strong>onion parcel</strong> to the other side of the tray and return the tray to the oven for a further 25 min or until the r\u00f6sti is golden and the sausage is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>sausage topped golden r\u00f6sti </strong>and <strong>sweet onions</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-golden-rosti-with-sausages-and-onion-gravy/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything is nearly ready, add your <strong>trimmed green beans</strong> to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them)</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pan with a little <strong>butter </strong>and keep covered until serving \u2013 these are your <strong>buttery green beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-golden-rosti-with-sausages-and-onion-gravy/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>gravy base </strong>with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> in a heatproof bowl, whisk thoroughly</p><p>Put the<strong> gravy base </strong>in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 30-40 secs or until thickened</p><p>Once thickened, add your <strong>sweet onions </strong>and give everything a good mix up (careful it may be hot!) \u2013 this is your <strong>onion gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-golden-rosti-with-sausages-and-onion-gravy/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sausage topped</strong> <strong>r\u00f6sti </strong>and drizzle over your <strong>onion gravy</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>buttery green beans </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped chives </strong>and a dollop of the <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
